bio.experienceSummary: Hello all! I am a recent graduate from Marywood University, where I studied architecture and was a college athlete. With my artistic and athletic background, I will be able to conduct hands-on activities ranging from arts and crafts to playing games outside and everything between! My previous experience in childcare consists of being a summer camp counselor for K-5th graders for 3 years. I also am qualified to care for newborns and toddlers if needed. I am CPR and First Aid certified. I am also a daughter and I understand the needs of parents and children, so I offer assistance in anyway you and your family may need with a happy heart!

bio.experienceSummary:
I am currently a toddler teacher. I have 14 children in my class between the ages of 2 and 3.
Over the summer I was an infant caregiver. I had 2-month-old babies up to 18 months.
I am CPR and first aid certified.
I have a clean background history.
I have been babysitting for family friends for certain occasions for 2 years.
I was also a lead assistant at a Montessori for 2 1/2 years, dealing with children ages 18 months - 6 years.

As a caregiver with over a decade of experience, my passion for caring for children stems from my positive babysitting experiences and my genuine desire to make a difference in their lives. I believe in supporting families and providing a dependable childcare option that allows parents peace of mind.

My patient, calm, and friendly nature allows me to connect with children effortlessly. I foster creativity and imagination through engaging activities, making each day an enriching experience.

Open and effective communication is key to my approach. Whether it's verbal updates during pickup, regular text messages, or phone calls, I ensure parents are informed about their child's day and any matters that arise.

I am exceptionally comfortable enforcing household rules, ensuring a safe and consistent environment for the children in my care.

From outdoor sports to board games and puzzles, I enjoy a wide range of games that cater to different interests and age groups.

bio.experienceSummary: Worked for a childcare center for 2 years and tutored children for 4+ years. CPR ad First Aid Certificed. Understand Spanish and Fluent in arabic.

I'm an educated, responsible, respectable, fun loving individual who truly enjoys working with children. I have 3 of my own whom I adore, and I would like the opportunity to help you care for yours.
My experience ranges from 0 month-12 years old. My experience with children started 18 years ago when I gained most of my experience working for a local daycare center where I worked for 4 years. Since then, I have worked pediatrics, I am currently with LVHN pediatrics in Easton full time. I'm fully vaccinated and hold all CPR and first aid certifications, as well as a government background check. 
I have had experience with Down Syndrome & Autistic children. 
I also do outdoor activities, help with homework ect. 
My experience working in families' homes has been wonderful. I'm fluent in English and Spanish. 
I'm okay with pets.

Hi! I'm Tayyabah! I am a reliable, responsible, and devoting caregiver who you can completely trust to take care of your children and ensure their safety. I am a college student majoring in Supply Chain Management who likes to bake, watch movies, and go for walks! I have been caring for children for over eight years and have experience taking care of children of all ages and personalities. I can do and help with various activities that your child may require. When I'm there, you can relax and expect to have your children under the best care a parent could wish for.

I'm single with no children, but I love children. It's so fun to be with them. Children is a precious gift from the Lord. Babysitting for kids is where my heart is. I am trustworthy, honest, responsible, dependable, helpful, energetic and fun-loving nanny. I have 15 years of experience as a full time nanny assisting kids for all ages.

description.originalText: Oce cared for our 1.5 year old daughter full time for a month. She was full of energy for our active little girl! We really appreciated Oce’s flexibility - she was always on time and willing to come early/stay late when my work schedule changed. Very glad we found Oce!

bio.experienceSummary:
Hi, my name is Jennifer. I am a former tenured teacher who stepped away to raise my family, awaiting the opportunity to return to the classroom and make a difference. I resumed teaching six years ago, as a teacher at the Westfield YMCA for children ages 1 through 3. When observing my classroom you would notice that all the children were engaged and most importantly having fun! I left that position in order to attend Rutgers University and received my Teacher of Students with Disabilities endorsement. This allowed me to secure my current position as a special education social studies teacher. As a successful teacher, I vary my instruction and classroom strategies to most effectively meet the divergent needs of my students. I have also applied these same principles over the last 19 years with my own children because as the mother of three teenagers, I pride myself on being warm, welcoming, enthusiastic, flexible, and attentive. 

Please message me about my summer availability.

Hello, I'm Kerri-Ann. I have a passion for working with children. I am currently a Part-Time Graduate student at Montclair State, majoring in Clinical Psychology with a concentration in child and adolescent studies. I've previously worked as an early educator at Kinder-care. I've also worked as a Behavioral Assistant, Youth Mentor, and Youth Counselor with children ages 5-17. Additionally, I currently work with different families on care. com as an ad-hoc sitter. I love what I do and will continue to provide care to children while I pursue my degree. My goal is to gain as much experiences as possible, build relationships with families, and pay my way through graduate school. I'm CPR, AED, and first-aid certified. I'm patient, reliable, caring, and supportive. Moreover, safety, wellness, and education is what I value most. Your child/children will be in great hands. I look forward to working with you. Thank you.

description.originalText: Kerri-Ann was great! She showed up on time and was great with my 8 month old. She was very thorough when learning about the schedule and responds quickly. We will definitely hire Kerri again!
